2
00:01:34,030 --> 00:01:38,990
[Regeneration]

3
00:01:39,030 --> 00:01:41,950
[Episode 2]

4
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:48,610
Wait,

5
00:01:49,690 --> 00:01:51,370
do you remember the location?

6
00:01:54,160 --> 00:01:56,120
Songshan Road.

7
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:57,250
Zhang...

8
00:01:57,440 --> 00:01:58,970
Zhanghua Road.

9
00:01:58,970 --> 00:02:00,440
What's the name of that community?

10
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:02,970
It's...

11
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:05,240
Something Haoting.

12
00:02:05,240 --> 00:02:06,170
Yujin Haoting.

13
00:02:08,290 --> 00:02:08,960
Right.

14
00:02:09,040 --> 00:02:09,650
Right...

15
00:02:09,650 --> 00:02:10,600
That's the place!

16
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,570
Room 701, Building Six.

17
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:18,240
How do you know?

18
00:02:23,730 --> 00:02:24,960
That's not his home.

19
00:02:27,810 --> 00:02:28,960
That's mine.

20
00:02:34,090 --> 00:02:35,170
Your home?

21
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:40,650
You mean, Fei Ke brought
people to your place

22
00:02:40,810 --> 00:02:42,760
and made it look like his?

23
00:02:43,210 --> 00:02:43,960
Yeah.

24
00:02:44,810 --> 00:02:45,880
Did you know that?

25
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:48,400
Not until today.

26
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:52,680
Let Mr. Chen finish first.

27
00:03:10,530 --> 00:03:11,120
Mr. Chen.

28
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:12,730
Jiajia.

29
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:14,730
Come in, please.

30
00:03:17,290 --> 00:03:18,400
It's... It's south-facing, right?

31
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:19,400
Right.

32
00:03:22,010 --> 00:03:23,040
What's the size of this place?

33
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:24,240
177 square meters,

34
00:03:24,320 --> 00:03:25,400
with a usable area of 140.

35
00:03:27,210 --> 00:03:29,600
The houses in this area go
for like 70 to 80 grand per sqm, right?

36
00:03:30,010 --> 00:03:31,880
I bought it early.
It was just over 50 thousand.

37
00:03:32,170 --> 00:03:33,120
I don't do property flipping

38
00:03:33,210 --> 00:03:34,320
and I wasn't too sensitive
to the prices.

39
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:36,040
Did you pay with cash or a loan?

40
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:37,120
Dad!

41
00:03:38,370 --> 00:03:39,570
My parents paid the down payment.

42
00:03:39,570 --> 00:03:40,570
And I'm paying off the mortgage.

43
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:41,810
How much a month?

44
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:44,600
I bought at a low rate,

45
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:45,730
less than four percent.

46
00:03:46,290 --> 00:03:48,810
The entire loan was 3.8 million,

47
00:03:49,010 --> 00:03:50,210
and the monthly repayment
is a little over 20 thousand.

48
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:54,290
So... 30 years?

49
00:03:54,370 --> 00:03:55,120
Twenty.

50
00:03:55,730 --> 00:03:56,930
I was outside the country

51
00:03:57,010 --> 00:03:58,320
and I bought it under my dad's name.

52
00:03:59,010 --> 00:04:00,210
He's almost 50.

53
00:04:00,370 --> 00:04:01,400
The term is at most 20 years.

54
00:04:02,010 --> 00:04:02,570
Mr. Chen.

55
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:04,960
Do you prefer tea or coffee?

56
00:04:05,090 --> 00:04:05,680
Tea.

57
00:04:06,090 --> 00:04:06,730
Okay.

58
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:31,370
Mr. Chen.

59
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:38,600
This is good tea.

60
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:42,090
Golden and clear.

61
00:04:42,650 --> 00:04:45,480
The leaves are neat and thick.

62
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:47,650
The taste is clean

63
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:48,930
and rich.

64
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:50,160
It's good tea.

65
00:04:51,130 --> 00:04:52,250
Mr. Chen, you know the deal.

66
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:55,530
This tea has got
to be five or six years, isn't it?

67
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:57,650
It's a national gift.

68
00:04:57,760 --> 00:04:59,000
Not for sale.

69
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,090
First-picked premium white peony
from eight years ago.

70
00:05:02,810 --> 00:05:03,760
Traditionally made.

71
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:05,090
No stir-frying, no rubbing.

72
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:06,090
It soothes the lungs.

73
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:08,930
I think you're the expert here!

74
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,880
I overheard some seniors talking

75
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:13,760
and I remembered it.

76
00:05:14,090 --> 00:05:15,130
Sorry for showing off.

77
00:05:16,370 --> 00:05:17,210
I'll check out the place a little more.

78
00:05:18,090 --> 00:05:18,930
I'll show you.

79
00:05:19,370 --> 00:05:20,160
Fei Ke...

80
00:05:20,210 --> 00:05:20,930
Listen!

81
00:05:21,370 --> 00:05:22,440
Whose apartment is this?

82
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:23,690
Mine.

83
00:05:24,250 --> 00:05:25,000
Cut it out!

84
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,280
It's true!

85
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:28,850
You can't be serious.

86
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:32,250
Check it out.

87
00:05:35,850 --> 00:05:36,970
This is my bedroom.

88
00:05:36,970 --> 00:05:38,130
Here's the closet.

89
00:05:41,970 --> 00:05:43,560
There's an open kitchen.

90
00:05:43,970 --> 00:05:45,130
This is the study.

91
00:05:45,970 --> 00:05:47,370
Best lighting in the place.

92
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:49,410
I'll have a smoke, okay?

93
00:05:49,530 --> 00:05:50,410
Okay, go ahead.

94
00:05:50,530 --> 00:05:51,130
Is that okay?

95
00:05:51,530 --> 00:05:52,040
Sure.

96
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:53,280
I'll go get you an ashtray.

97
00:05:59,690 --> 00:06:00,280
Here.

98
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:04,480
Make yourself at home. I'll go cook.

99
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:05,440
Okay, go ahead.

100
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:06,000
Okay.

101
00:06:13,130 --> 00:06:14,250
Here, see if you like my cooking.

102
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:15,690
Okay...

103
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:17,600
Here.

104
00:06:18,210 --> 00:06:20,000
To our first meeting
and your achievement.

105
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:20,650
Cheers.

106
00:06:24,280 --> 00:06:25,970
It's a nice apartment.

107
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,210
Why don't you live here?

108
00:06:27,210 --> 00:06:29,040
It's too far from my office.

109
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:31,090
I thought you had a car?

110
00:06:31,530 --> 00:06:32,650
It wasn't mine, actually.

111
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:33,810
It belongs to my mom.

112
00:06:34,690 --> 00:06:36,040
Strictly speaking,

113
00:06:36,810 --> 00:06:38,090
I own nothing.

114
00:06:40,250 --> 00:06:42,480
Well, what's your parents'
is eventually yours.

115
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:43,650
Not the same.

116
00:06:44,130 --> 00:06:45,090
When I bought this place,

117
00:06:45,090 --> 00:06:46,440
my dad was working in Chengjiang.

118
00:06:46,850 --> 00:06:47,970
When the apartment was delivered,

119
00:06:47,970 --> 00:06:49,280
he got transferred to Beijing.

120
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:53,090
I'm now technically
managing their property.

121
00:06:53,530 --> 00:06:54,880
And you kept me in the dark, too.

122
00:06:55,130 --> 00:06:56,090
If I hadn't done that,

123
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:57,560
you wouldn't be living
with your dad, would you?

124
00:07:00,090 --> 00:07:02,760
Well, I've actually
been longing to kick her out!

125
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:05,210
Start a family, will you?

126
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:08,440
By the way...

127
00:07:10,280 --> 00:07:12,690
What do your parents do?

128
00:07:15,810 --> 00:07:17,160
They're just ordinary public servants.

129
00:07:18,690 --> 00:07:19,600
In which department?

130
00:07:21,370 --> 00:07:23,690
Dad, would you stop interrogating?

131
00:07:24,130 --> 00:07:25,090
Stay out of it.

132
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:28,090
Mr. Chen.

133
00:07:28,130 --> 00:07:29,480
You're no stranger here,

134
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:30,850
but

135
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:32,970
I'd have to ask you to keep it a secret.

136
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:36,000
I'm no big mouth, okay?

137
00:07:37,970 --> 00:07:39,480
Management Department,
Ministry of Lands and Mines.

138
00:07:42,410 --> 00:07:44,970
Let me see. Management Department?

139
00:07:45,970 --> 00:07:47,690
First name... Fei?

140
00:07:48,210 --> 00:07:49,480
I took after my mom.

141
00:07:50,810 --> 00:07:52,280
And your dad's first name?

142
00:07:52,410 --> 00:07:53,160
Li.

143
00:07:56,280 --> 00:07:58,160
What does your mom do?

144
00:07:58,440 --> 00:07:59,560
She's a college teacher.

145
00:07:59,850 --> 00:08:02,370
Not a 985 university, just a 211.

146
00:08:02,650 --> 00:08:03,410
She's a professor.

147
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:05,600
All she does is read papers.

148
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:06,650
Kind of boring.

149
00:08:06,810 --> 00:08:08,090
Good.

150
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:09,280
An intellectual.

151
00:08:09,320 --> 00:08:10,440
She's got the insight.

152
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:14,280
Wait.

153
00:08:15,250 --> 00:08:17,810
She's a college teacher

154
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:18,720
and she drives...

155
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:20,320
a Panamera?

156
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:24,760
Well, that,

157
00:08:24,810 --> 00:08:26,560
that was a used test-drive car
from my uncle's shop.

158
00:08:26,930 --> 00:08:28,160
I don't drive it often, either.

159
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:28,970
Jiajia knows that.

160
00:08:29,970 --> 00:08:32,360
Plus, the parking space
in my office building

161
00:08:32,410 --> 00:08:34,210
costs 60 yuan an hour!

162
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:37,050
I figured I might as well live closer,

163
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,170
so I'd save some money.

164
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,530
Yeah...

165
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:42,050
So, um...

166
00:08:42,050 --> 00:08:44,730
Where... Where's the place you rented?

167
00:08:45,410 --> 00:08:47,000
It's a staff dormitory
of Chengjiang University.

168
00:08:47,410 --> 00:08:48,610
It's an old building,

169
00:08:48,610 --> 00:08:49,880
but I like the environment.

170
00:08:50,290 --> 00:08:51,680
I could just walk to their library.

171
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:54,410
I think that's the top living environment
you can buy!

172
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:56,440
Well said!

173
00:08:58,650 --> 00:09:00,730
Be efficient
while keeping a low profile!

174
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:02,210
Come on!

175
00:09:02,210 --> 00:09:02,760
Mr. Chen.

176
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:04,730
- Mr. Chen.
- No need!

177
00:09:05,530 --> 00:09:06,320
Come on, take it.

178
00:09:06,490 --> 00:09:08,000
No need. He's got a lot already.

179
00:09:08,610 --> 00:09:10,240
Take it. I don't drink tea myself.

180
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:12,120
If they send me more,

181
00:09:12,170 --> 00:09:14,090
I'll have Jiajia bring it to you.

182
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:16,730
But... That's too polite of you.

183
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:17,410
It's...

184
00:09:18,210 --> 00:09:19,170
No need!

185
00:09:20,410 --> 00:09:21,610
Snob.

186
00:09:23,650 --> 00:09:25,730
I'm just concerned.

187
00:09:25,850 --> 00:09:27,610
I want you to have a nice life.

188
00:09:30,050 --> 00:09:33,210
But this guy
is quite something indeed.

189
00:09:33,530 --> 00:09:34,650
And he's solid, isn't he?

190
00:09:35,410 --> 00:09:36,680
Well, it's fate.

191
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:39,000
I guess you have met your fate.

192
00:09:39,290 --> 00:09:41,560
So, you've agreed to our marriage?

193
00:09:42,610 --> 00:09:43,490
No.

194
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:45,680
Even though I've agreed,

195
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:47,730
as a girl,

196
00:09:48,530 --> 00:09:50,320
you need composure.

197
00:09:51,050 --> 00:09:51,560
Dad!

198
00:09:51,850 --> 00:09:53,440
What more do you have to worry about?

199
00:09:58,290 --> 00:10:00,320
Well, he's said a lot,

200
00:10:00,970 --> 00:10:03,000
but we need to see it to believe it.

201
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:05,360
At least...

202
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:07,650
I need to see his parents, right?

203
00:10:13,230 --> 00:10:14,150
[Ministry of Lands and Mines]

204
00:10:15,050 --> 00:10:15,760
Mr. Chen,

205
00:10:16,090 --> 00:10:17,210
I checked.

206
00:10:17,210 --> 00:10:18,880
There is a Deputy Director General
surnamed Li.

207
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:19,920
Born in 1960.

208
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,850
I found some photos for you.

209
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:29,490
Got it.

210
00:10:29,490 --> 00:10:30,560
So,

211
00:10:30,850 --> 00:10:32,290
the two of them should be a good match?

212
00:10:33,610 --> 00:10:35,560
More like they worked in cahoots to me.

213
00:10:38,650 --> 00:10:41,120
Mr. Chen, have you seen his parents?

214
00:10:43,410 --> 00:10:44,320
In a month,

215
00:10:45,410 --> 00:10:47,530
I met his family.

216
00:10:48,090 --> 00:10:49,800
His father meant to come,

217
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:51,880
but

218
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:54,050
got stuck in Beijing

219
00:10:54,730 --> 00:10:56,440
for some important conference.

220
00:10:56,610 --> 00:10:58,290
I had dinner with his mother.

221
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:00,920
It was at my own club.

222
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,120
We had a great time chatting that day.

223
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:04,000
Please, sit here.

224
00:11:04,620 --> 00:11:05,000
Nice to meet you!

225
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:07,290
His mother is a gentle person.

226
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:08,800
Good-mannered and knowledgeable.

227
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:09,970
Mr. Chen, we're family now.

228
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:11,050
Go easy on the drink.

229
00:11:11,050 --> 00:11:12,290
Mr. Chen, still?

230
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:13,610
Call me Fa.

231
00:11:13,610 --> 00:11:14,530
Fa is fine.

232
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:17,850
Once I saw this future in-law,

233
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:22,360
I knew that my girl would be
in good hands.

234
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:24,800
Give us a grandson soon.

235
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:26,970
Well, that depends on Jiajia.

236
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:29,530
Me and my husband wouldn't demand that.

237
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:32,360
A son is a must.

238
00:11:32,490 --> 00:11:34,170
A son can do big things!

239
00:11:34,880 --> 00:11:35,730
Either is okay.

240
00:11:35,730 --> 00:11:37,800
You see, don't you have
a great daughter here?

241
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:39,050
Aren't you proud?

242
00:11:39,170 --> 00:11:41,050
Come on, your son is great too.

243
00:11:41,210 --> 00:11:42,000
Yeah.

244
00:11:43,050 --> 00:11:43,610
Fei Ke.

245
00:11:45,170 --> 00:11:46,970
Do bring words to your dad, okay?

246
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:49,290
I understand
that it's inconvenient for him

247
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:50,920
to meet us merchants right now.

248
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:53,530
Some day,

249
00:11:53,970 --> 00:11:56,610
I'll definitely invite him to dinner.

250
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:59,120
It's a touchy moment.

251
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:01,120
And my dad is indeed at a conference.

252
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:02,210
He couldn't come.

253
00:12:03,970 --> 00:12:05,680
That's more important...

254
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:11,000
I heard that they're correcting
rented accounts,

255
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,050
is that true?

256
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:15,120
Well, I don't know the specifics,

257
00:12:15,530 --> 00:12:17,000
but rented accounts

258
00:12:17,210 --> 00:12:18,490
do have...

259
00:12:19,210 --> 00:12:21,090
security issues

260
00:12:21,210 --> 00:12:23,170
and mining qualification issues,

261
00:12:23,290 --> 00:12:24,650
which the leaders are focusing on.

262
00:12:27,530 --> 00:12:28,610
I also heard

263
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:33,920
that they're retracting
all mining licenses

264
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:36,610
to re-examine before distributing them?

265
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:37,850
I don't know.

266
00:12:38,560 --> 00:12:39,610
But...

267
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:42,730
there are over a thousand
rented account companies in the country.

268
00:12:43,090 --> 00:12:44,760
A thorough check

269
00:12:44,880 --> 00:12:45,850
would take time, right?

270
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:48,360
Fei Ke,

271
00:12:49,170 --> 00:12:51,210
how old is your dad?

272
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:52,440
Fifty-five.

273
00:12:52,680 --> 00:12:53,650
Born in 1960.

274
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:56,210
1960?

275
00:12:56,410 --> 00:12:57,210
What's his Zodiac?

276
00:12:57,920 --> 00:12:58,680
Pig.

277
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:00,050
Wait.

278
00:13:00,170 --> 00:13:01,760
Isn't 1960...

279
00:13:02,290 --> 00:13:03,680
Rat?

280
00:13:04,210 --> 00:13:07,530
My dad was born on December 17
by the lunar calendar

281
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:08,880
and January 15 by the solar calendar.

282
00:13:09,410 --> 00:13:09,850
Yes...

283
00:13:09,850 --> 00:13:11,680
So, he takes on the Year 1959,
the Pig Year.

284
00:13:12,850 --> 00:13:13,800
Born in the 60s.

285
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:15,490
That's a good age.

286
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:17,680
He's got potential.

287
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:19,000
You know what?

288
00:13:19,610 --> 00:13:20,290
Son,

289
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:22,410
